Sentencas: Platinum electrodes for high temperature electrochemical devices (solid oxide fuel cells, solid oxide electrolyzer cells and sensors) generally show limited performances due to confinement of triple phase boundaries.
Titulo: Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Symmetrical Pt-YSZ Electrodes Prepared by YSZ Infiltration
Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Symmetrical Pt-YSZ Electrodes Prepared by YSZ Infiltration

Sentencas: Performance degradation as a result of TPB length loss due to the microstructural instability of the Platinum electrodes at operational temperatures is the other major problem.
Titulo: Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Symmetrical Pt-YSZ Electrodes Prepared by YSZ Infiltration

Sentencas: Infiltration of yttrium stabilized zirconia (YSZ) into porous Platinum electrodes using polymeric metal-oxide precursor was utilized as a prospective solution to these problems.
Titulo: Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Symmetrical Pt-YSZ Electrodes Prepared by YSZ Infiltration

Sentencas: It was shown that this process formed a YSZ coating on the Platinum particle surface which led to significantly increased effective contact area between Platinum electrodes and the electrolyte, and prevented the coarsening of Platinum.
Titulo: Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Symmetrical Pt-YSZ Electrodes Prepared by YSZ Infiltration

Sentencas: Symmetrical cells with YSZ infiltrated Platinum electrodes showed polarization resistance of 0.045 Ohm.cm(2) per cathode at 800 degrees C, in air.
Titulo: Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Symmetrical Pt-YSZ Electrodes Prepared by YSZ Infiltration

Sentencas: In fuel cell operation mode, the total electrode polarization resistance (anode cathode) was 0.35 Ohm.cm(2) at 800 degrees C and 0.130 Ohm.cm(2) at 900 degrees C. Power densities of 0.45 Watt/cm(2) and 0.9 Watt/cm(2) at 800 degrees C and 900 degrees C were obtained respectively.
Titulo: Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Symmetrical Pt-YSZ Electrodes Prepared by YSZ Infiltration

Sentencas: No degradation of the cell was observed for the duration of measurement (248 hours).
Titulo: Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Symmetrical Pt-YSZ Electrodes Prepared by YSZ Infiltration
